-07-15T16:20:02Z"",""IsDeleted"":""0"",""SourceEventId"":""1072"",""ImageId"":null,""Slug"":""furry_fandom_in_turkey"",""Title"":""Furry Fandom in Turkey: The Beginning"",""SubTitle"":"""",""ConferenceTrackId"":""4007871e-893b-45b1-87a8-9c15949279f0"",""Abstract"":""Tarkan the Wolf will talk about his achievements in building a furry community in his homeland, Turkey, over the past 4-5 years.  "",""Description"":""Tarkan the Wolf has invested time in building up a furry community in Turkey. He wants to show the audience what he achieved so far and what is planned for this star-up community in the future. The project started around 5 years ago and was promoted to the Anime fandom first as well as to \""geeky\/nerdy\"" young people in the country. \r\nFuture plans include local furmeets beginning next year and the very first Turkish furry convention in 2020 taking place in Istanbul. Hear every interesting fact about it in this talk!"",""ConferenceDayId"":""8af3def1-2b00-11e6-af7b-066e23d209cf"",""StartTime"":""10:00:00"",""EndTime"":""11:30:00"",""Duration"":""01:30:00"",""ConferenceRoomId"":""370977a9-22a5-4255-ae98-58125391c0f0"",""PanelHosts"":""Tarkan the Wolf"",""IsDeviatingFromConBook"":""0""},{""Id"":""8679fe19-fb2f-40e3-91c0-7d32442a4163"",""LastChangeDateTimeUtc"":""2016-07-15T17:40:02Z"",""IsDeleted"":""0"",""SourceEventId"":""970"",""ImageId"":null,""Slug"":""fsps_reg_6"",""Title"":""Fursuit Photoshoot Registration "",""SubTitle"":""Block 6"",""ConferenceTrackId"":""8af35b1a-2b00-11e6-af7b-066e23d209cf"",""Abstract"":""Registration is done at the main registration desk, first come first serve. Each block in the schedule has its own registration time, \""Block 2\"" registration is only for \""Block 2\"" openings! Once all slots for a block are taken, registration is closed again. The \""to time\"" is thus a \""approximate up until\"" time. Due to the large request for timeslots, we need to prefer those who didn't get a chance the year before. You can still apply, but you might get turned back."",""Description"":""Registration is done at the main registration desk, first come first serve. Each block in the schedule has its own registration time, \""Block 2\"" registration is only for \""Block 2\"" openings! Once all slots for a block are taken, registration is closed again. The \""to time\"" is thus a \""approximate up until\"" time. Due to the large request for timeslots, we need to prefer those who didn't get a chance the year before. You can still apply, but you might get turned back."",""ConferenceDayId"":""8af3f161-2b00-11e6-af7b-066e23d209cf"",""StartTime"":""11:00:00"",""EndTime"":""12:00:00"",""Duration"":""01:00:00"",""ConferenceRoomId"":""7e3dad60-fee6-4ab8-b1be-a99655ec4218"",""PanelHosts"":""shorty"",""IsDeviatingFromConBook"":""0""},{""Id"":""872c70a4-6ef3-411e-b518-3b2be1e64b3c"",""LastChangeDateTimeUtc"":""2016-07-15T16:30:02Z"",""IsDeleted"":""0"",""SourceEventId"":""1043"",""ImageId"":null,""Slug"":""furry_lightning_talks"",""Title"":""Furry Lightning Talks "",""SubTitle"":""Free for all!"",""ConferenceTrackId"":""4007871e-893b-45b1-87a8-9c15949279f0"",""Abstract"":""This is your panel! Share your passion, project or thought in this fast-paced event. Every speaker has 5 minutes to present their topic. Join us to see the fandom from different viewpoints. If you want to, you can even share your own story. Spontanous presentations welcome!"",""Description"":""Not everything warrants a whole 60 or 90 minute panel. Maybe you want to share this cute furry game you found online or tell the story of how you found your fursona. After all, your passions, projects and unique thoughts are what makes Eurofurence truly magical.\r\n\r\nIn this panel, everyone gets their time to present their story. Feel free to come by to see different aspects of the fandom from many viewpoints. If you want to, you can even share your own thoughts: Spontaneous presentations are welcome!"",""ConferenceDayId"":""8af3d567-2b00-11e6-af7b-066e23d209cf"",""StartTime"":""21:00:00"",""EndTime"":""00:00:00"",""Duration"":""03:00:00"",""ConferenceRoomId"":""a602eb0c-4e24-4e74-a5e9-479fd7cddef5"",""PanelHosts"":""Fenmar"",""IsDeviatingFromConBook"":""0""},{""Id"":""8868579f-83f4-4866-b830-ab5a0e3d8140"",""LastChangeDateTimeUtc"":""2016-07-14T17:10:02Z"",""IsDeleted"":""0"",""SourceEventId"":""1082"",""ImageId"":null,""Slug"":""world_building_101"",""Title"":""World Building 101"",""SubTitle"":"""",""ConferenceTrackId"":""111331da-f230-4731-ab94-648ca846bb9d"",""Abstract"":""You're not just writing - you're telling a story in the context of a world. The science fiction and fantasy \r\ngenres are rich on strange worlds and fantastic settings - some more believable than others. But\r\nwhat makes these exotic places seem real? What makes the reader want to visit and explore them?"",""Description"":""You're not just writing - you're telling a story in the context of a world. The science fiction and fantasy \r\ngenres are rich on strange worlds and fantastic settings - some more believable than others. But\r\nwhat makes these exotic places seem real? What makes the reader want to visit and explore them?\r\n\r\nWriters seem to spend a lot of time developing details that never appear in the final works. Is that \r\nreally necessary, or can you write straight away and make up details as you go? Why such an excessive \r\nbackground when swordfights are so much more exciting!\r\n\r\nHow do authors avoid writing their worlds as bad copies of other works, or collections of boring tropes?\r\nDiscover the heart of worldbuilding in this panel."",""ConferenceDayId"":""8af3def1-2b00-11e6-af7b-066e23d209cf"",""StartTime"":""14:00:00"",""EndTime"":""15:30:00"",""Duration"":""01:30:00"",""ConferenceRoomId"":""a602eb0c-4e24-4e74-a5e9-479fd7cddef5"",""PanelHosts"":""Cairyn"",""IsDeviatingFromConBook"":""0""},{""Id"":""8af40fcd-2b00-11e6-af7b-066e23d209cf"",""LastChangeDateTimeUtc"":""2016-06-05T09:33:21Z"",""IsDeleted"":""0"",""